# Keycloak + Supabase Integration

## How This Integration Works (Simple Explanation)

```
WITHOUT INTEGRATION (now):
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
User → Supabase Auth (its own login system)
User → Keycloak (separate login)
Two separate auth systems = mess

WITH INTEGRATION (goal):
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
User → Keycloak (ONE login)
         ↓ issues JWT token
Supabase → "I trust Keycloak tokens"
         ↓ validates token
AIOps Data → accessible only if token valid

Flow:
1. User logs into Keycloak
2. Gets JWT token
3. Sends token to Supabase API
4. Supabase verifies token with Keycloak
5. Data returned or access denied
```

