## Step 3: Configure Token Claims (VERY IMPORTANT)

Supabase needs specific claims inside the JWT token. We add them via Client Scopes.

```
Keycloak UI:
Clients → supabase → Client scopes tab
Click: supabase-dedicated
Click: Add mapper → By configuration
Choose: User Attribute
```

Add these mappers one by one:

**Mapper 1 — role claim:**
```
Mapper type:      User Realm Role
Name:             roles
Token Claim Name: role
Claim JSON Type:  String
Add to ID token:          ON
Add to access token:      ON
Add to userinfo:          ON
Save
```

**Mapper 2 — email claim:**
```
Mapper type:      User Property
Name:             email
Property:         email
Token Claim Name: email
Claim JSON Type:  String
Add to access token: ON
Save
```

