## Step 4: Get Keycloak JWT Public Key

Supabase needs this to verify tokens are real.

```bash
# Get your Keycloak route URL
KEYCLOAK_URL=$(oc get route keycloak \
  -n moizaleem21-dev \
  -o jsonpath='{.spec.host}')

# Fetch the JWKS (public keys) endpoint
curl -s https://$KEYCLOAK_URL/realms/aiops-dev/protocol/openid-connect/certs \
  | python3 -m json.tool

# Save this URL — needed for Supabase config:
echo "JWKS URL: https://$KEYCLOAK_URL/realms/aiops-dev/protocol/openid-connect/certs"

# Also get the JWT issuer URL:
echo "Issuer URL: https://$KEYCLOAK_URL/realms/aiops-dev"
```

---

## Step 5: Get RSA Public Key (PEM format)

```bash
# Fetch public key in PEM format
curl -s https://$KEYCLOAK_URL/realms/aiops-dev \
  | python3 -c "
import sys, json, base64, textwrap
data = json.load(sys.stdin)
key = data['public_key']
pem = '-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\n'
pem += '\n'.join(textwrap.wrap(key, 64))
pem += '\n-----END PUBLIC KEY-----'
print(pem)
" > /tmp/keycloak-public-key.pem

# Show the key
cat /tmp/keycloak-public-key.pem

# Copy this entire key — needed for Supabase values.yaml
```

