# PHASE 3 — Database Row Level Security (RLS)

## Step 11: Enable RLS on Supabase Tables

This ensures only Keycloak-authenticated users can access AIOps data:

```bash
# Connect to Supabase PostgreSQL
SUPA_DB_POD=$(oc get pods -n moizaleem21-dev \
  | grep -i "supabase.*db\|postgres" \
  | awk '{print $1}' | head -1)

oc exec -it $SUPA_DB_POD \
  -n moizaleem21-dev -- psql -U postgres
```

Inside psql run these SQL commands:

```sql
-- ============================================================
-- STEP 1: Create custom JWT validation function
-- This reads role from Keycloak JWT token
-- ============================================================
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION auth.jwt_role()
RETURNS text AS $$
  SELECT coalesce(
    current_setting('request.jwt.claims', true)::json->>'role',
    'anon'
  )
$$ LANGUAGE sql STABLE;

-- ============================================================
-- STEP 2: Example — Enable RLS on your AIOps data table
-- ============================================================
-- Enable RLS on table (replace 'aiops_events' with your table)
ALTER TABLE public.aiops_events ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- Policy: only authenticated users can read
CREATE POLICY "authenticated users can read aiops data"
  ON public.aiops_events
  FOR SELECT
  USING (auth.jwt_role() = 'authenticated');

-- Policy: only ml-engineer role can insert
CREATE POLICY "ml engineers can insert data"
  ON public.aiops_events
  FOR INSERT
  WITH CHECK (
    current_setting('request.jwt.claims', true)::json
    ->'realm_access'->'roles' @> '["ml-engineer"]'
  );

-- Policy: only aiops-admin can delete
CREATE POLICY "admins can delete"
  ON public.aiops_events
  FOR DELETE
  USING (
    current_setting('request.jwt.claims', true)::json
    ->'realm_access'->'roles' @> '["aiops-admin"]'
  );

-- Verify RLS is enabled
SELECT tablename, rowsecurity
FROM pg_tables
WHERE schemaname = 'public';
```

