# Summary of What We Did

```
INTEGRATION ARCHITECTURE:
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

AIOps Service / User
        ↓
   1. Login to Keycloak
        ↓
   2. Get JWT Token (contains role: ml-engineer etc.)
        ↓
   3. Call Supabase API with token in header
        ↓
   4. Supabase verifies token signature with
      Keycloak public key
        ↓
   5. PostgREST checks Row Level Security policies
        ↓
   6. Only correct role gets data back

KEYCLOAK SIDE:
  ✅ supabase client created
  ✅ role claim added to JWT token
  ✅ JWKS endpoint exposed for Supabase

SUPABASE SIDE:
  ✅ Keycloak as OIDC provider
  ✅ JWT verification against Keycloak
  ✅ Row Level Security on AIOps tables

DATABASE SIDE:
  ✅ RLS enabled on tables
  ✅ Policies per Keycloak role
  ✅ Only authenticated users see data
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
```

